# Titanic Dataset: Data Cleaning & Preprocessing

![Titanic](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/RMS_Titanic_3.jpg/1200px-RMS_Titanic_3.jpg)

This project demonstrates a complete data cleaning and preprocessing pipeline for the Titanic dataset, preparing it for machine learning tasks.

## Table of Contents
- [Project Overview](#project-overview)
- [Dataset Description](#dataset-description)
- [Cleaning Steps](#cleaning-steps)
- [How to Run](#how-to-run)
- [Results](#results)
- [Dependencies](#dependencies)

## Project Overview
This project covers:
- Handling missing values
- Converting categorical features
- Normalizing numerical features
- Outlier detection and treatment

## Dataset Description
The Titanic dataset contains information about 891 passengers including:
- Survival status (Survived)
- Passenger class (Pclass)
- Age, Sex, Fare
- Embarkation port (Embarked)
- Cabin information

Original dataset from [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic/data)

## Cleaning Steps

### 1. Missing Value Treatment
- Age: Filled with median value
- Embarked: Filled with most frequent value (mode)
- Cabin: Dropped (too many missing values)

### 2. Categorical Encoding
- Sex: Label encoded (male=0, female=1)
- Embarked: One-hot encoded

### 3. Feature Scaling
- Age and Fare standardized using StandardScaler

### 4. Outlier Handling
- Fare outliers capped using IQR method
- Visualized with boxplots before/after treatment

## How to Run
1. Clone this repository
2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn
